sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User / kubectl
    participant APIServer as K8s API Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Webhook as Training Operator Webhook<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS TLS (self-signed)
    participant Operator as Training Operator Controller<br/>opendatahub namespace
    participant Pods as Worker Pods<br/>user namespace
    participant HeadlessSvc as Headless Service<br/>ClusterIP=None
    participant Monitoring as OpenShift Monitoring<br/>8080/TCP HTTP

    Note over User,Monitoring: Flow 1: Training Job Lifecycle (PyTorch/TF/XGBoost/Paddle/JAX)

    User->>APIServer: POST /apis/kubeflow.org/v1/{jobtype}<br/>Auth: User credentials
    APIServer->>Webhook: POST /validate-kubeflow-org-v1-{jobtype}<br/>HTTPS/9443, TLS (self-signed)
    Webhook-->>APIServer: Admission Response (allow/deny)
    APIServer-->>User: Job CR created

    Note over Operator: Informer detects new CR

    Operator->>APIServer: Create Pods (workers)<br/>HTTPS/443, ServiceAccount token
    Operator->>APIServer: Create Headless Service<br/>HTTPS/443, ServiceAccount token
    Operator->>APIServer: Create NetworkPolicy (PyTorch only)<br/>HTTPS/443, ServiceAccount token

    Note over Pods,HeadlessSvc: Workers discover each other via DNS

    Pods->>HeadlessSvc: DNS lookup: {job}-{type}-{index}<br/>Framework port/TCP
    Pods->>Pods: Training data exchange<br/>Framework port/TCP, No encryption

    Note over Operator: Monitors pod status via informers

    Operator->>APIServer: Update Job status<br/>HTTPS/443, ServiceAccount token

    Monitoring->>Operator: GET /metrics<br/>HTTP/8080, No auth

    Note over User,Monitoring: Flow 2: MPI Job Execution (Asymmetric Pattern)

    User->>APIServer: POST /apis/kubeflow.org/v1/mpijobs<br/>Auth: User credentials
    APIServer-->>User: MPIJob CR created

    Operator->>APIServer: Create ConfigMap (hostfile, kubexec.sh)<br/>HTTPS/443
    Operator->>APIServer: Create ServiceAccount + Role + RoleBinding<br/>HTTPS/443
    Operator->>APIServer: Create Worker Pods<br/>HTTPS/443
    Operator->>APIServer: Create Launcher Pod (with kubectl init container)<br/>HTTPS/443

    Note over Pods: Launcher runs mpirun

    Pods->>APIServer: kubectl exec into workers<br/>HTTPS/443, Launcher SA token
    APIServer->>Pods: exec stream to worker pods<br/>TLS 1.2+

    Note over User,Monitoring: Flow 3: PyTorch Elastic Training

    Operator->>APIServer: Create HorizontalPodAutoscaler<br/>HTTPS/443
    Pods->>Pods: c10d rendezvous on Master/Worker-0<br/>29500/TCP, No encryption
    Note over APIServer: HPA scales worker replicas
    Operator->>APIServer: Reconcile pods after scale event<br/>HTTPS/443
